+<h1>Getting Started<a class="headerlink" href="#getting-started" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h1>
 <p>The software <em>Diacamma Pro</em> includes a large number of settings and few seem difficult to configure to need your structure.</p>
 <p>We offer this explanation to help you take that first step in using this tool.</p>
 <p>Follow step by step the various phases settings. In each step, we will not re-show the features.
 We also invite you to refer to the rest user manual for it.</p>
 <p>It may be interesting to perform backups during this procedure.
 This will allow you, if you made a mistake, to return to a previous step without starting everything (including installation).</p>
 <section id="check-the-last-days-of-your-software">
-<h2>Check the last days of your software<a class="headerlink" href="#check-the-last-days-of-your-software" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Check the last days of your software<a class="headerlink" href="#check-the-last-days-of-your-software" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h2>
 <p>Start by checking your software is up to days.
 Indeed, we regularly distribute patches that are not always included in the installers.</p>
 </section>
 <section id="presentation-of-your-structures">
-<h2>Presentation of your structures<a class="headerlink" href="#presentation-of-your-structures" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Presentation of your structures<a class="headerlink" href="#presentation-of-your-structures" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h2>
 <blockquote>
 <div><p>Menu <em>General/Our details</em></p>
 </div></blockquote>
 <p>In this screen, you can describe the details of your structure.
 Many features use this information especially for impressions (invoices, accounting, members of the list …)</p>
 </section>
 <section id="adjusting-your-invoice">
-<h2>Adjusting your invoice<a class="headerlink" href="#adjusting-your-invoice" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Adjusting your invoice<a class="headerlink" href="#adjusting-your-invoice" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h2>
 <blockquote>
 <div><p>Menu <em>Management/Modules (conf.)/Payoff configuration</em>
 Menu <em>Management/Modules (conf.)/Invoice configuration</em></p>
 </div></blockquote>
 <p>Make sure the settings match your invoice.
 You can also here, set up the bank details of your main bank account as well as add secondary.
 These will be helpful for functionality “check deposit” the biller.</p>
 </section>
 <section id="creating-your-first-fiscal-year">
-<h2>Creating your first fiscal year<a class="headerlink" href="#creating-your-first-fiscal-year" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Creating your first fiscal year<a class="headerlink" href="#creating-your-first-fiscal-year" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h2>
 <blockquote>
 <div><p>Menu <em>Management/Modules (conf.)/Accounting Configuration</em>
 Menu <em>Financial/Bookkeeping/charts of account</em></p>
 </div></blockquote>
 <p>Craft your first fiscal year and make it active.
 You will also create accounts this year to have a fully operational accounting.</p>
 </section>
 <section id="accounting-update">
-<h2>Accounting update<a class="headerlink" href="#accounting-update" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Accounting update<a class="headerlink" href="#accounting-update" title="Permalink to this heading">¶</a></h2>
 <blockquote>
 <div><p>Menu <em>Financial/Bookkeeping/accounting entries</em>
 Menu <em>Financial/Bookkeeping/Model of entry</em></p>
 </div></blockquote>
 <p>If you implement <em>Diacamma asso</em> during your exercise, you will also need to enter your retained earnings of the previous year and reenter the writings of earlier this year.</p>
 <p>Warning: do not forget that adding a membership fee generates an invoice and associated accounting entries. Take into account the recovery of your accounts.
 To help you entering your accounting, we advise you to use the scriptures models. Register entant model recurring entries that you have in a year. So you can quickly complete your accounting few clicks.</p>
 </section>

 </div></blockquote>
 <p>Define your settings for your email.
 The smtp server allow <em>Diacamma Asso</em> sent to a number of message: invoice in PDF, connection password …</p>
 <p>You can specify how to react links ‘write to all’ react with your email software.</p>
 </section>

 <p><em>Diacamma Pro</em> is a management software specifically designed for very small business.</p>
 <p>The basic application is completely free and allows you to manage access to your data and the address book of your association. Add-ons allow you to adjust a few clicks the software to your needs.</p>
 <p>The different available modules allow you, for example, to:</p>

 <p>You can install <em>Diacamma Pro</em> on a dedicated computer to your association either an Apple Macintosh (OS X 10.8 and up) or a PC running MS-Windows (7 and up) or GNU Linux (Ubuntu 14.04 or +).</p>
 <p><em>Diacamma Pro</em> is a client/server software: you can install it on a centralized computer and access data from another PC connected to the first, with no limit on the number of simultaneous users.
 If the PC containing the data is permanently connected to the Internet, you can access your data from anywhere in the world!</p>
 <p>This organization is particularly attractive to allow more associative executives to access common data.</p>
 <p>What manager has not ripped the hair after a document exchange via USB stick where some important changes are lost?</p>

+    performObjectSearch: (object, objectTerms) => {
+        const filenames = Search._index.filenames;
+        const docNames = Search._index.docnames;
+        const objects = Search._index.objects;
+        const objNames = Search._index.objnames;
+        const titles = Search._index.titles;
+
+        const results = [];
+
+        const objectSearchCallback = (prefix, match) => {
+            const name = match[4]
+            const fullname = (prefix ? prefix + "." : "") + name;
+            const fullnameLower = fullname.toLowerCase();
+            if (fullnameLower.indexOf(object) < 0) return;
+
+            let score = 0;
+            const parts = fullnameLower.split(".");
+
+            // check for different match types: exact matches of full name or
+            // "last name" (i.e. last dotted part)
+            if (fullnameLower === object || parts.slice(-1)[0] === object)
+                score += Scorer.objNameMatch;
+            else if (parts.slice(-1)[0].indexOf(object) > -1)
+                score += Scorer.objPartialMatch; // matches in last name
+
+            const objName = objNames[match[1]][2];
+            const title = titles[match[0]];
+
+            // If more than one term searched for, we require other words to be
+            // found in the name/title/description
+            const otherTerms = new Set(objectTerms);
+            otherTerms.delete(object);
+            if (otherTerms.size > 0) {
+                const haystack = `${prefix} ${name} ${objName} ${title}`.toLowerCase();
+                if (
+                    [...otherTerms].some((otherTerm) => haystack.indexOf(otherTerm) < 0)
+                )
+                    return;
+            }
+
+            let anchor = match[3];
+            if (anchor === "") anchor = fullname;
+            else if (anchor === "-") anchor = objNames[match[1]][1] + "-" + fullname;
+
+            const descr = objName + _(", in ") + title;
+
+            // add custom score for some objects according to scorer
+            if (Scorer.objPrio.hasOwnProperty(match[2]))
+                score += Scorer.objPrio[match[2]];
+            else score += Scorer.objPrioDefault;
+
+            results.push([
+                docNames[match[0]],
+                fullname,
+                "#" + anchor,
+                descr,
+                score,
+                filenames[match[0]],
+            ]);
+        };
+        Object.keys(objects).forEach((prefix) =>
+            objects[prefix].forEach((array) =>
+                objectSearchCallback(prefix, array)
+            )
+        );

 <section id="description">
-<h2>Description<a class="headerlink" href="#description" title="Lien permanent vers ce titre">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Description<a class="headerlink" href="#description" title="Lien permanent vers cette rubrique">¶</a></h2>
 <p><em>Diacamma Pro</em> est un logiciel de gestion spécialement conçu pour les TPE et les micro-entreprise.</p>
 <p>L’application de base est entièrement gratuite et vous permet de gérer les accès à vos données et au carnet d’adresses de votre association. Les modules complémentaires vous permettront d’adapter en quelques clics le logiciel à vos besoins.</p>
 <p>Les différents modules disponibles vous permettront, par exemple, de:</p>
 <blockquote>
 <div><ul class="simple">
 <li><p>Gérer vos documents de façon centralisée grâce à la gestion documentaire.</p></li>
 <li><p>Gérer la comptabilité de votre association.</p></li>
 <li><p>Gérer vos devis, factures et factures proformat pour les adhérents subventionnés par un CE, entre autre.</p></li>
 </ul>
 </div></blockquote>
 <p>Ce manuel vous aidera dans l’utilisation de ce logiciel.
 Si malgré tout, vous ne trouvez pas la réponse à vos problèmes, visiter notre site <a class="reference external" href="https://www.diacamma.org">https://www.diacamma.org</a> où vous trouverez des tutoriels et des astuces.</p>
 </section>
 <section id="installation">
-<h2>Installation<a class="headerlink" href="#installation" title="Lien permanent vers ce titre">¶</a></h2>
+<h2>Installation<a class="headerlink" href="#installation" title="Lien permanent vers cette rubrique">¶</a></h2>
 <p>Vous pouvez installer <em>Diacamma Pro</em> sur un ordinateur dédié à votre association que ce soit un Apple Macintosh (macOS 10.12 « Sierra » et +) ou bien un PC sous MS-Windows (8 et +) ou sous GNU Linux (Ubuntu 16.04 ou +)..</p>
 <p><em>Diacamma Pro</em> est un logiciel client/serveur : vous pouvez l’installer sur un ordinateur centralisateur et accéder aux données depuis un autre PC connecté au premier, sans limite du nombre d’utilisateurs simultanés.
 Si le PC contenant les données est connecté de manière permanente à internet, vous aurez accès à vos données depuis n’importe où dans le monde!</p>
 <p>Cette organisation est particulièrement intéressante pour permette à plusieurs cadres associatifs d’avoir accès à des données communes.</p>
 <p>Quel responsable ne s’est pas arraché les cheveux suite à un échanges de documents via une clef USB où certaines modifications importantes se perdent?</p>
 <p>Pour plus d’information, visiter notre site <a class="reference external" href="https://www.diacamma.org">https://www.diacamma.org</a></p>
 </section>

 <p>Si vous souhaitez un service et un support plus personnalisé, vous pouvez faire confiance à notre partenaire officiel SLETO.
 Pour en savoir plus sur des solutions d’hébergement et de support, rendez vous sur <a class="reference external" href="https://www.sleto.net">https://www.sleto.net</a></p>
